    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="608"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d608">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5612/19</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Netherland Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cremer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 6</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of December 4, 1918, in which you inform the Department that your <pb
                        facs="0736" n="651" xml:id="pg_651"/> Government is anxious to extend for
                    another period of five years the Arbitration Convention of May 2, 1908, extended
                    by agreement of May 4 [<hi rend="italic">9</hi>], 1914, and which will expire on
                    March 25, 1919.</p>
                <p>The draft of agreement enclosed with your note is satisfactory to the Department
                    of State, which will prepare the agreement for signature and notify you of the
                    time fixed for that ceremony.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Acting Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
